parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to latch or unlatch
the shoulder straps do not hold in place
the release button fails
the buckle breaks
the seat belt comes out of the buckle
difficulty fastening the seat belt
the seat belt will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The buckle breaks
the plastic release button fails
the buckle will not release
the buckle locks in place
difficulty fastening the seat belt
the buckle comes apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not latch
the seat belt comes out of the buckle
difficulty fastening the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded, especially in heavy traffic or while driving on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle dies or stalls at stops
easily starts up again
requires putting the transmission in park to restart
and may have no warning signs before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: The engine overheats
especially when the air conditioning is in use
and may cause the secondary engine fan to melt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain or belt failure can cause the engine to stall or become inoperable, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The timing chain or belt breaks
causing the engine to stall immediately
and may be accompanied by a loud noise or engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and rust can cause engine components to fail, leading to engine stalling, overheating, or other issues.
symptoms: Freeze plugs corrode
causing water to leak out of the engine
and mufflers rust.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Wear on Bushings and Frame Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive wear on bushings and frame damage can cause the vehicle to drift or pull to one side, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle drifts or pulls to one side while driving
uneven tire wear
and abnormal noises from the suspension system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission malfunction can cause the vehicle to jump forward in lower gears, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps forward in lower gears
sudden acceleration
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective rear struts can cause uneven tire wear, leading to reduced traction and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Premature wear on rear tires
uneven tire wear
and vibration or noise from the rear suspension system.
